It is concluded by the analysis presented in this letter that the first period of the Covid-19 epidemic, before the herd immunity, may be interpreted in terms of simple models containing physically meaningful parameters. The temporal evolution of the total number of cases may be divided to three phases. In the f phase, it is shown that the number of new cases depends on the total number of cases in a power-law relation with an exponent \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
